Saga of House Ellesarien<br>
<br>
Chapter One - Loss<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Sandalorn, Watch the mounts little brother&quot;, Dannen spoke over his shoulder as the elven hunting party disappeared into the Emerald Forest around them.<br>
&quot;But I never get to come along&quot; Sandalorn replied moodily. This was the sixth hunting party this month that he had to stay behind and watch the mounts as his brothers and the rest of the hunting party struck back against the slow tide of goblins and orcs which threatened to invade the forest around their ancient ancestral home; ‘Tor Anrouk’.<br>
Dannen’s laughter wafted back to him from the surrounding forest “You are not yet ready brother. Don’t you worry; you will wet your swords soon enough.”<br>
<br>
Scowling and muttering under his breath, Sandalorn steadied his nerves and thoughts while he tried to calm himself to find the “Any’llia’. Loosely translated to mean ‘Peace’ in the Common tongue, The ‘Any’llia’ was the place his father and brothers told him their weapon mastery came from. A place where time slowed and body and mind worked in sync to harness the Ellesarien power and might. Their house was of an ancient lineage; one of the first families created by Tunare. In fact, they were one of the only Elven Houses still able to hear the thoughts of Tunare from her residence in the Plane of Growth. The ‘Any’llia’ was a thought from Tunare, a piece of her love that House Ellesarien could call upon to heighten their battle senses and movements.<br>
<br>
As he started to move through his lessons and stances, the ‘Any’llia’ gently washed over Sandalorn. As he became closer to his Goddess, his thoughts and movements became sharper and more defined. From one stance to the next, he moved around the clearing in a dance of blades; the silver reflection of the moon glancing off his swirling twin swords. In his heightened state, the distance yells of fighting penetrated his concentration. As he slowed his dance and listened closer, he could hear a wild commotion and the angry screams of many orcs far away in the forest. He smiled to himself as he thought about his three brothers dealing out damage and death to their evil foes. Dannen, Grefanix, and Trelot were all very watchful over him he knew. They tried to prevent him from entering the councils and meetings that they and their father, Inglorian, held about the orc and goblin hordes. But Sandalorn had found a way around that a while ago and now listened in to all their palavers through the small hole in the ceiling where he lay perched for hours upon end. He knew that things were growing worse and soon an all out war would wage through the Ellesarien lands.<br>
<br>
Suddenly the entire forest exploded in a vile red light; throwing corrupted reflections of the noble trees of the Emerald Forest down across Sandalorn. The distant screams of the orcs quickly changed to chants and battle cries. Sandalorn knew that something unexpected had happened and quickly got the horses ready in case the hunting party returned in haste. More explosions and flashes of the evil red light echoed across the forest as teems of wildlife burst into the clearing and past him.<br>
<br>
“Sandalorn!!” his brother Trelot’s voice exploded in his mind. “You must take the horses and flee..Now! We are overrun by…..something evil…I do not know what it is. But we are overpowered and dropping quickly. We will meet up with you at the mill”. <br>
<br>
It had been years since one of his brothers had used the ‘Meshing’ to contact him in his mind. The link contained emotions too…Pain and fear washed upon him as the link transferred his brother’s feelings to him. The sudden intensity of emotions brought Sandalorn to one knee, shaking his head and trying to stay conscious as his mind struggled to regain its footing. He could not leave his kin, his brothers, his family. He would not run when they were in danger.<br>
<br>
“No Trelot” he thought back across the link. “I will not run. I will hold the horses for you here. Come quickly”.<br>
<br>
“You fool!” his brother screamed into his mind. “We probably won’t even make it back to the horses. Flee now for your life. Evil is in these woods and we are undone.”<br>
<br>
“I will not abandon you brother” Sandalorn replied quietly. The “Any’llia” was absorbing itself into him again, washing away his fear and anxiety. “I will be here with the horses when you return”.<br>
<br>
“Fool” Trelot spoke again. “We are close. Be ready then little brother; for we bring death along with us”.<br>
<br>
The quiet ring of steel being drawn was Sandalorn’s only reply. He waited, poised for battle in the clearing as he heard destruction draw closer. Suddenly Grefanix dashed into the clearing, blood streaming from multiple wounds and from his….ears?<br>
<br>
“We are in dire straights Sandalorn” Grefanix breathed through gasps as he tried to catch his breath. “Something is out there…Something evil like I have never seen. We are doomed I believe, but you are not!”. With that Grefanix grabbed Sandalorn and started to stuff dirt in his ears, quickly cutting out all sound.<br>
<br>
“What are you doing?” Sandalorn exclaimed. “Have you gone mad?”.<br>
<br>
Grefanix’s reply was barely heard “I am saving you little brother. Now run fast and don’t look back”<br>
<br>
Sandalorn reply was cut off as hell entered the clearing. His two other brothers; Dannen and Trelot, burst into the clearing along with two others from the elven hunting party. “Just five left” Sandalorn whispered to himself. What in the name of Tunare is happening?”<br>
<br>
His question was soon answered as a creature walked slowly into the clearing. He was huge; 14ft. easily and surrounding by a flowing red cape. He seemed to be playing some type of musical instrument and singing loudly. Only the dirt stuffed into Sandalorn’s ears prevented him from really hearing what the creature was singing. <br>
<br>
His three brothers and the other two elven hunters all collapsed to the ground, holding their ears tightly as blood poured from them. Sandalorn stood stunned as his life shattered down around him.<br>
<br>
“Poor elves” the creature spoke haughtily. Sandalorn could just barely hear him through his clogged ears. “You have incurred the wrath of my master and now your punishment is at hand. This forest has been claimed in his name and you stop his plan for going forth with your killing of his minions. But you will be repaid ten-fold! For he has sent me to do his bidding and my wrath is unquenchable. No ones escapes the Maestro of Rancor!!”<br>
<br>
The creature turned his burning eyes to Sandalorn. “What have we here? Another little elf for the slaughter. Good…we can always use more. But why are you still standing? Can you not hear my beautiful music?”<br>
<br>
“Flee little brother…Flee now!” Dannen’s voice entered his mind. Dannen’s voice was quiet and intense. “You can’t save us. We are dying already. His music is death and we have listened. Go to father and tell him what happened. GO NOW!”<br>
<br>
Sandalorn took one quick last glance as his brothers and ran. Dannen’s voice brooked no compromise. He must tell father. He could hear nothing as he ran and ran through the forest, heading towards the mill where their backup mounts rested. He was getting near the mill when he turned around a tree and ran smack directly into the flat of a sword blade.<br>
<br>
The last thing he heard before darkness swarmed in was his brothers screams in his head……<br>
